Question: Develop an argument for or against the following statement: television violence is appropriate for audiences of all ages
Answer:
Television violence is only appropriate for mature audiences who understand the context in which the violence or violent act took place. Without this context, the young or immature viewer might misunderstand what he is watching. Even mature audience movies, however, should only have violence of it significantly advances the plot or is otherwise needed. Gratuitous violence is unhealthy for any age.